election_record.label: Vermont 1822 U.S. House of Representatives

overview.note: The Official Results list Rollin C. Mallory with 17242 votes, Samuel C. Crafts with 15825 votes, Charles Rich with 13617 votes, Daniel Azro Buck with 10151 votes, William C. Bradley with 9816 votes, John Mattocks with 6772 votes, Elias Keyes with 5712 votes, Steven Haight, Jr. with 3855 votes, Phineas White with 2961 votes, Orasmus C. Merrill with 1184 votes and Horace Everett with 1060 votes but the county totals add up to 17660 votes for Mallory, 16253 votes for Crafts, 13732 votes for Rich, 10176 votes for Buck, 9911 votes for Bradley, 6864 votes for Mattocks, 5773 votes for Keyes, 3715 votes for Haight, 2959 votes for White, 1204 votes for Merrill and 1065 votes for Everett.
